data.name: skipHistoryChk.ToolTip
data.value: If enabled, skip reconversion will also check the history file for past conversions. The expected filename for the converted video (not the original video filename) is compared with the filenames in the history file. If the to be converted filename (including path) matches any of the already converted filenames (including paths) in the history file, the file will not be reconverted and it will be assumed to be a successful conversion.

data.name: skipReprocessChk.ToolTip
data.value:
Do not reconvert the video if a converted file already exists in the destination directory. The expected filename for the converted video (not the original video filename) is compared with the filenames in the destination directory. If the converted file exists, the file will not be reconverted and it will be assumed to be a successful conversion. This is useful if the same show/episode is being recorded on multiple times and you don't want to reconvert them.
NOTE: This option is ignored for videos that are added manually using the add button or dragging and dropping

data.name: monitorTaskNameMatchChk.ToolTip
data.value: Check this box if you want this conversion task to only process files from specific monitor locations. If unchecked each conversion task will process files from all monitor locations (including new ones added later).

data.name: commercialSkipCutChk.ToolTip
data.value: Check this if you want MCEBuddy to detect the ads (commercials) but NOT cut them from the video. When this option is enabled, MCEBuddy will create an EDL file along with the converted file that specifies the locations of ads in the converted video. Also, for MP4, M4V and MKV files MCEBuddy will create Chapters to mark the end of commercials.

data.name: disableCroppingChk.ToolTip
data.value: Check this to disable cropping the video automatically during conversion. Cropping is used to remove the "black bars" in the video (top, bottom, left or right). Use this option if the video picture is getting cut on any side or if the final picture is looking stretched or distorted.

data.name: audioOffsetChk.ToolTip
data.value: Enter a value in seconds (positive or negative) here to shift the audio relative to the video. Use this to resync the audio with the video, if they are out of sync after conversion. A positive value will delay the audio (i.e. video ahead of audio) and a negative value will advanced the audio (i.e. audio ahead of video). E.g. -1.5

data.name: skipCopyChk.ToolTip
data.value: CHECK THIS BOX AT YOUR OWN RISK. DO NOT CHECK THIS BOX UNLESS YOU KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING. Check this box to skip making a backup of original file (copying) while converting. If this is checked, the original file will not be preserved in case of an error. It can also even lead to conversion failures or other unforeseen conversion issues.

data.name: forceShowTypeLbl.ToolTip
data.value: Set this to force treating the video recording as a Movie or TV Series. This will change the way additional information (metadata) about the recording is downloaded from the internet. Movie - Treat the recording as movie Series - Treat the recording as a TV Series Sports - Treat the recording as a Sports show Default - Use the default information available in the recording metadata to determine Movie or TV Series

data.name: ignoreCopyProtectionChk.ToolTip
data.value: Check this to ignore the copy protection flag on video file while converting. NOTE: MCEBuddy cannot bypass encryption, this only helps if a file is incorrectly tagged as copy protected when it is NOT encrypted.

data.name: insertTopChk.ToolTip
data.value: By default, new conversions are added to the bottom (end) of the conversion queue. If this box is checked, any new conversions added by this task will be added to the beginning (top) of the conversion queue.

data.name: embedSrtChaptersChk.ToolTip
data.value:
Enable this option to add any extracted subtitles and chapters to the converted video. Each chapter marks the end of a commercial. This only works with supported formats (e.g. MKV, MP4).
NOTE: Some players and older TV's don't support embedded subtitles and chapters. If you're unable to playback the converted video's, try turning this option off.

data.name: drcChk.ToolTip
data.value: Dynamic Range Compression (DRC) When the source is an AC3 audio, enabling DRC will reduce the difference between the loud and the soft sounds making the audio track more even. If you have a multi-channel audio recording and you feel the volume is too soft, checking this box might help.

data.name: writeMetadataChk.ToolTip
data.value:
Check this box to write the metadata extracted from the orginal file and downloaded from the internet into the converted file. This only works for files that support metadata tags like MP4, MKV, WTV etc.
NOTE: Uncheck this box if you're facing issues with some devices such as older TV's which have problem reading metadata.

data.name: frameRateChk.ToolTip
data.value:
Enable this to set a custom framerate (FPS) for the converted video. You may need to set this while converting video formats (e.g. PAL to NTSC) or for devices which support only specific framerates.
E.g.: 25 E.g.: 30000/1001

data.name: skipRemuxChk.ToolTip
data.value: CHECK THIS BOX AT YOUR OWN RISK. DO NOT CHECK THIS BOX UNLESS YOU KNOW WHAT YOU ARE DOING. Check this box to skip remuxing the original file to a TS file while converting. If this is checked, some functions like subtitle extraction or comskip may not work. It can also even lead to conversion failures or other unforeseen conversion issues.

data.name: hardwareEncodingChk.ToolTip
data.value:
Check this box to use hardware encoding when available to convert videos. This can speed up the conversion significantly and reduce the CPU utilization but it can result in slightly lower quality videos.
Uncheck this box if you're facing conversion or quality issues.

data.name: drmFilterLbl.ToolTip
data.value:
Selection based on Digital Right Management (DRM) is available only when Rename without converting (Rename and move only) option is selected.
All - Selects all files for processing, irrespective of copy protection status Protected - Only select files which are copy protected Unprotected - Only select files which do not have copy protection
